verbose_text: CSNK2A1, encoding an alpha catalytic subunit of protein kinase CK2, promotes tumor cell growth, adhesion and migration by activating the Janus kinase / signal transducer and activator of transcription, nuclear factor-kappaB, PI3K / AKT, Hsp90, Wnt and Hedgehog pathways.
evidence: adhesion and migration by activating the Janus kinase/signal transducer and activator of transcription
